              - kind: EndOfLineComment
                text: "'A hash is a 'fingerprint' of any string."
              - kind: Newline
                text: "\n"
              - kind: EndOfLineComment
                text: "'Hashes are extremely useful for determining whether a"
              - kind: Newline
                text: "\n"
              - kind: EndOfLineComment
                text: "'transmission or file has been altered.  This code can use"
              - kind: Newline
                text: "\n"
              - kind: EndOfLineComment
                text: "'one of two algorithms (see note above).  No matter what the"
              - kind: Newline
                text: "\n"
              - kind: EndOfLineComment
                text: "'length of input data, the hash will be a fixed length and"
              - kind: Newline
                text: "\n"
              - kind: EndOfLineComment
                text: "'will be unique for that string of data.  The same hash is produced for"
              - kind: Newline
                text: "\n"
              - kind: EndOfLineComment
                text: "'the same input data every time.  This is useful here to"
              - kind: Newline
                text: "\n"
              - kind: EndOfLineComment
                text: "'produce a fixed-length, unique password for any length password entered."
              - kind: Newline
                text: "\n"
